# Copy to .env and adjust.

# Local dev: SQLite file (default).
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# Vercel / Turso (libsql) — required for production deploy. `file:` SQLite does not work on Vercel serverless.
# Create a DB at https://turso.tech → copy libsql URL and token, then push schema: `npx prisma db push`
# (with the same DATABASE_URL and TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN in your shell).
# DATABASE_URL="libsql://your-db-yourname.turso.io"
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN="..."

# In Vercel project settings, set at least: DATABASE_URL (libsql), TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN, AUTH_SECRET (32+ chars).

# Session signing (JWT). Use a long random string (32+ chars). Required in production.
# AUTH_SECRET="your-secret-at-least-32-characters-long"

# OpenAI — invoice draft from work description (gpt-4o-mini by default).
# OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
# OPENAI_MODEL="gpt-4o-mini"

# Set to 1 to preview the create-invoice flow with sample line items (no OpenAI call, no API key).
# Put in `.env` or `.env.local` at the project root, then restart `npm run dev`.
# In `next dev` you can also use the on-page checkbox "Use sample line items" (no env required).
# SOLOBILL_MOCK_INVOICE_AI=1

# Public hosted demo: skip login for a shared user (e.g. GitHub / Vercel). Never enable for private data.
# Create that user in the database first, e.g. `npx tsx scripts/seed-dev-user.ts` (or match SOLOBILL_DEMO_USER_EMAIL).
# SOLOBILL_PUBLIC_DEMO=1
# SOLOBILL_DEMO_USER_EMAIL="demo@solobill.local"
